3. How to install project

	With a linux bash shell, make you're way to the project directory.
	Inside this directory there will be a makefile which can be excuted using the "make" 		command.
	When this command is excuted within the directory there will be a file created called 		"Lab2EX".
	Use this command "./Lab3EX" to run the file.

4. List of any required Libraries, platform issues, etc.

	Source code - C++
	Makefile use - g++ compiler


5. TO DO section listing items that need to be completed (errors, missing features etc.)

6. List of files and what they contain

	main.cpp: The main file that will create two tasks on individual threads 
	Makefile: Instructions to compile source code
	Semaphore.cpp: Implementation for semaphore
	Semaphore.h: Header file of Semaphore.cpp
	
